OL,4,CWomen could be owed 'lottery-winning'
OL,5,Cpension sums
OL,6, Women on #1-a-week state pensions could
OL,7, be owed tens of thousands of pounds,
OL,8, the BBC has learned.
OL,10,FUntil recently, Carole Davies, 76, from
OL,11,FMerstham in Surrey, was told she was
OL,12,Fentitled to less than #1 a week.
OL,14,F"When I retired in 2003, my state
OL,15,Fpension was so low - 40p a week - I was
OL,16,Ftold that it would be paid once a
OL,17,Fyear," she told BBC Radio 5 Live.
OL,19,F"Despite my husband Michael questioning
OL,20,Fthis after he retired in 2005, we were
OL,21,Ftold I wasn't due anything more."
